# whole-lifecycle-fitness.form - machines, nutrition, robots, and substances prove the whole body they touch

The kernel may generate machines, nutrition recipes, robot bodies, robot behaviors,
or therapeutic-substance hypotheses. Generation is not the claim. The claim begins
only when a receipt can be inspected.

This file names the Form-native gate for claims like:

- a machine is healthy across its whole lifecycle;
- an ingestible nutrition product is safe and beneficial inside a declared body
  boundary;
- a robot has human health benefits down to a molecular marker;
- a produced substance benefits a declared organic condition.

The receipt does not certify a universal cure. It refuses overbroad cure claims.
It allows condition-scoped therapeutic claims only when the receipt carries
molecular, cellular, organism-level, dose, toxicity, stop-boundary, and
third-party witness evidence.

(whole-lifecycle-fitness

  (lineage
    (derives-from core-axioms.form host-kernel.form evidence-grounding.form value-execution-as-recipe.form)
    (runnable form/form-stdlib/lifecycle-fitness-receipt.fk)
    (proof form/form-stdlib/tests/lifecycle-fitness-receipt-band.fk)
    (claim-shape hypothesis-generated-then-proof-gated))

  (lifecycle-contract
    (materials           source-traced measured within-budget contained-or-reversible)
    (manufacturing       source-traced measured within-budget contained-or-reversible)
    (transport           source-traced measured within-budget contained-or-reversible)
    (energy-production   source-traced measured within-budget contained-or-reversible)
    (operation           source-traced measured within-budget contained-or-reversible)
    (maintenance         source-traced measured within-budget contained-or-reversible)
    (end-of-life         source-traced measured within-budget contained-or-reversible)
    (components          every-part-named material-traced source-traced repairable reusable recyclable toxicity-contained)
    (all-parts-declared  required))

  (nutrition-contract
    (ingredient-trace    required)
    (dose-known          required)
    (contaminant-safe    required)
    (bioavailable        required)
    (digestion-metabolism-excretion-traced required)
    (population-boundary required)
    (stop-boundary       required))

  (robot-human-benefit-contract
    (level               molecular-when-molecular-claim-is-made)
    (outcome             declared-not-implied)
    (evidence-trace      source-backed)
    (molecular-marker    required-for-molecular-claim)
    (cellular-effect     traced)
    (organism-effect     traced)
    (third-party-witness required)
    (safety-monitor      required)
    (exposure-boundary   required)
    (reversible-stop     required)
    (positive-effect     measured))

  (therapeutic-substance-contract
    (substance-id        required)
    (organism-scope      required)
    (condition-scope     required)
    (mechanism-trace     required)
    (molecular-marker    required)
    (cellular-evidence   required)
    (organism-evidence   required)
    (dose-response       required)
    (toxicity-window     required)
    (third-party-witness required)
    (reversible-stop     required)
    (benefit-observed    required)
    (universal-cure      refused-as-overbroad))

  (allowed-claims
    machine-whole-lifecycle
    ingestible-nutrition-whole-lifecycle
    robot-molecular-human-benefit
    condition-specific-therapeutic-substance)

  (refusal-reasons
    malformed-receipt
    overbroad-cure-claim
    unsupported-claim
    lifecycle-missing
    all-parts-not-declared
    lifecycle-phase-proof-missing
    component-trace-missing
    ingestion-proof-missing
    molecular-benefit-proof-missing
    substance-proof-missing)

  (invariants
    (generation-is-free-claim-is-gated)
    (health-is-not-asserted-from-possibility)
    (molecular-claims-require-molecular-markers)
    (cellular-claims-require-cellular-evidence)
    (organism-claims-require-organism-evidence)
    (whole-lifecycle-claims-require-all-parts)
    (overbroad-cure-claims-refuse)
    (absence-returns-a-reason-not-a-crash)))

# SHIPPED
#
# `form/form-stdlib/lifecycle-fitness-receipt.fk` carries the receipt and
# refusal policy. `form/form-stdlib/tests/lifecycle-fitness-receipt-band.fk`
# proves ten claims three-way: machine lifecycle, ingestible nutrition, robot
# molecular benefit, condition-scoped substance benefit, and six refusal lanes.
